articles.title: Australia's IAG sees natural hazard claim costs at $280 million for first half
articles.description: Insurance Australia Group Ltd on Friday pegged net claim costs from natural disasters at A$400 million ($279.36 million) for the first half of fiscal 2020 in the wake of a deadly season of bushfires in the country.

articles.title: Bunge sells stake in U.S. ethanol plant as biofuels industry struggles
articles.description: Bunge Ltd ended its 13-year ownership interest in an Iowa ethanol plant, the company said on Thursday, following industry struggles with thin margins and overproduction.
articles.content:
